The paper deals with relation extraction, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a novel neural architecture for end-to-end relation extraction that utilizes metric-based features, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG). The architecture also involves 2D convolutions, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
